# Documentation Standards

## Technical Documentation
- Use precise technical language, avoid marketing speak
- Include implementation details and trade-offs
- Reference specific files using [filename.ext](mdc:filename.ext) format
- Document performance characteristics (latency, cost, quality metrics)

## Architecture Documentation
- Follow the structure established in [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:ARCHITECTURE.md)
- Include code examples with proper TypeScript syntax
- Document configuration options and their impact
- Explain why architectural decisions were made

